comment: R-Slash shows Mbah a Moute (PHI) cleanly defends Gasol (CHI), who loses control of the ball.
Video angles are inconclusive, but it appears that Moore (CHI) cleanly strips the ball from Smith (PHI), hitting either the ball or Smith's hand while it's in contact with the ball.
Gasol (CHI) defends Canaan (PHI) legally by following his path to the basket and maintaining a vertical position when he jumps.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the original ruling that possession be awarded to PHI was overturned and the possession given to CHI.
LHH shows Noel (PHI) beats Gasol to the point of contact and that his attempt to hit the ball does not make contact with Gasol (CHI) as he starts his shooting movement.
Brooks (CHI) jumps into Smith (PHI) as he drives to the basket, affecting his ability to take the shot.
Thompson's (PHI) contact with Snell (CHI) is incidental to his effort to block his shot.
LATR shows Brooks (CHI) dislodge Grant (PHI) on rebound attempt.
LHH shows contact by Gasol (CHI) on Canaan (PHI) during layup attempt is incidental to his effort to play him and does not affect his ability to take the shot.
Gasol (CHI) sets the screen on Smith (PHI) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
RATH shows Mirotic (CHI) is jumping toward Canaan (PHI) when contact occurs during Mirotic's shooting motion.
Canaan (PHI) contact with Dunleavy (CHI) during drive is incidental to his attempt to play him and does not affect his shooting motion.
Noel (PHI) sets the screen on Hinrich (CHI) without giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction, which results in a trip.
Grant (PHI) commits a take foul on Mirotic (CHI).
Noel (PHI) commits a take foul on Snell (CHI).
RATH shows Gasol (CHI) is in a legal guarding position when he defends Covington (PHI) as he drives to the basket and does not hit him with his off arm.
